{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NfCxfWAFt1pbHVf2zrqEZr","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 9.1: Workflow Patch Resolution\n2\t\n3\tStatus: backlog\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a developer,\n10\tI want to patch the default workflow via a patch file,\n11\tso that I can customize execution without replacing the entire workflow.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** an embedded default workflow at `templates/workflows/default.yaml` and a project-level patch file at `.codeharness/workflows/default.patch.yaml` with `extends: embedded://default`\n16\t   **When** the workflow resolver runs\n17\t   **Then** the patch's `overrides` are deep-merged onto the embedded base (objects merge recursively, arrays and scalars replace)\n18\t   **And** the resolved workflow still validates against the workflow JSON schema\n19\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n20\t\n21\t2. **Given** a patch with a `replace` key containing a top-level section (e.g., `replace: { flow: [...] }`)\n22\t   **When** the workflow resolver merges the patch\n23\t   **Then** the `replace` sections wholly overwrite the corresponding base sections (no deep merge, full replacement)\n24\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n25\t\n26\t3. **Given** no patch file exists at the user-level or project-level path\n27\t   **When** the workflow resolver runs\n28\t   **Then** the embedded default workflow is returned unchanged\n29\t   **And** no errors are thrown\n30\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n31\t\n32\t4. **Given** a patch file with invalid YAML syntax\n33\t   **When** the workflow resolver attempts to load it\n34\t   **Then** a `WorkflowParseError` is thrown with a descriptive message including the file path and parse error\n35\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n36\t\n37\t5. **Given** a patch file that is valid YAML but produces an invalid workflow after merge (e.g., references a non-existent task in flow)\n38\t   **When** the workflow resolver merges and validates\n39\t   **Then** a `WorkflowParseError` is thrown with specific schema or referential integrity errors\n40\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n41\t\n42\t6. **Given** both a user-level patch at `~/.codeharness/workflows/default.patch.yaml` and a project-level patch at `.codeharness/workflows/default.patch.yaml`\n43\t   **When** the workflow resolver runs\n44\t   **Then** the user-level patch is applied first onto the embedded base, and the project-level patch is applied second on top of the user-merged result\n45\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n46\t\n47\t7. **Given** `run.ts` currently loads the workflow via `parseWorkflow()`\n48\t   **When** this story is implemented\n49\t   **Then** `run.ts` calls a new `resolveWorkflow()` function (or equivalent) that handles the full embedded -> user -> project patch chain\n50\t   **And** `parseWorkflow()` remains available for direct file parsing (no breaking change)\n51\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n52\t\n53\t8. **Given** the `resolveWorkflow()` function\n54\t   **When** called with a `cwd` option\n55\t   **Then** it looks for project patches relative to `cwd` and user patches relative to `$HOME`\n56\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n57\t\n58\t9. **Given** `npm run build` is executed\n59\t   **When** the build completes\n60\t   **Then** it succeeds with zero errors\n61\t   **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n62\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n63\t\n64\t10. **Given** unit tests for workflow patch resolution\n65\t    **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n66\t    **Then** tests pass at 80%+ coverage for new code covering: patch loading, silent skip on missing, malformed patch errors, deep merge, replace semantics, user-before-project ordering, schema validation after merge, referential integrity after merge\n67\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n68\t\n69\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n70\t\n71\t- [ ] Task 1: Add `resolveWorkflow()` function to `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` (AC: #1, #3, #6, #7, #8)\n72\t  - [ ] Define `WorkflowPatch` interface: `{ extends?: string; overrides?: Record<string, unknown>; replace?: Record<string, unknown> }`\n73\t  - [ ] Implement `loadWorkflowPatch(filePath: string): WorkflowPatch | null` — reads patch YAML, returns null if file missing, throws `WorkflowParseError` on malformed YAML (mirrors `loadPatch` from agent-resolver)\n74\t  - [ ] Implement `mergeWorkflowPatch(base: Record<string, unknown>, patch: WorkflowPatch): Record<string, unknown>` — deep-merges `overrides`, then applies `replace` sections as full overwrites\n75\t  - [ ] Implement `resolveWorkflow(options?: { cwd?: string; name?: string }): ResolvedWorkflow` — loads embedded default from `templates/workflows/{name}.yaml`, applies user patch from `~/.codeharness/workflows/{name}.patch.yaml`, applies project patch from `.codeharness/workflows/{name}.patch.yaml`, then validates and returns\n76\t  - [ ] Reuse `deepMerge` utility — extract from agent-resolver into a shared location or duplicate inline (agent-resolver already has this pattern)\n77\t\n78\t- [ ] Task 2: Update `src/commands/run.ts` to use `resolveWorkflow()` (AC: #7)\n79\t  - [ ] Replace the existing `parseWorkflow(workflowPath)` call with `resolveWorkflow({ cwd: projectDir })`\n80\t  - [ ] Keep fallback logic for direct file path if `resolveWorkflow` fails (graceful degradation)\n81\t\n82\t- [ ] Task 3: Write unit tests in `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-parser.test.ts` (AC: #9, #10)\n83\t  - [ ] Test: `resolveWorkflow` returns embedded workflow when no patches exist\n84\t  - [ ] Test: `resolveWorkflow` deep-merges `overrides` from project patch onto embedded base\n85\t  - [ ] Test: `resolveWorkflow` applies `replace` sections as full replacement (not deep merge)\n86\t  - [ ] Test: `resolveWorkflow` applies user patch before project patch (ordering)\n87\t  - [ ] Test: `resolveWorkflow` throws `WorkflowParseError` for malformed YAML patch\n88\t  - [ ] Test: `resolveWorkflow` throws `WorkflowParseError` when merged result fails schema validation\n89\t  - [ ] Test: `resolveWorkflow` throws `WorkflowParseError` when merged result has dangling task refs in flow\n90\t  - [ ] Test: `resolveWorkflow` silently skips missing patch files\n91\t  - [ ] Test: `loadWorkflowPatch` returns null for non-existent file\n92\t  - [ ] Test: `loadWorkflowPatch` throws for invalid YAML\n93\t  - [ ] Test: `mergeWorkflowPatch` handles overrides-only patch\n94\t  - [ ] Test: `mergeWorkflowPatch` handles replace-only patch\n95\t  - [ ] Test: `mergeWorkflowPatch` handles patch with both overrides and replace\n96\t  - [ ] Test: existing `parseWorkflow` tests still pass (no regressions)\n97\t\n98\t- [ ] Task 4: Verify build and all tests pass (AC: #9)\n99\t  - [ ] Run `npm run build` — zero errors\n100\t  - [ ] Run `npm run test:unit` — no regressions\n101\t\n102\t## Dev Notes\n103\t\n104\t### Architecture Context\n105\t\n106\tPer architecture-v2.md (AD1), `workflow-parser` is responsible for: \"Parse YAML, validate against JSON schema, resolve patches (embedded->user->project)\" covering FR13-15. The patch resolution for workflows follows the same pattern as `agent-resolver.ts` does for agents.\n107\t\n108\tThe current `workflow-parser.ts` handles parsing and validation but has no patch resolution. This story adds the patch chain — the same embedded -> user -> project pattern that `agent-resolver.ts` already implements for agent configs.\n109\t\n110\t### Patch Chain (mirrors agent-resolver)\n111\t\n112\tResolution order:\n113\t1. Load embedded workflow from `templates/workflows/{name}.yaml`\n114\t2. Look for user-level patch at `~/.codeharness/workflows/{name}.patch.yaml` — merge if found, skip silently if not\n115\t3. Look for project-level patch at `.codeharness/workflows/{name}.patch.yaml` — merge if found, skip silently if not\n116\t4. Validate merged result against JSON schema + referential integrity\n117\t5. Apply defaults and return `ResolvedWorkflow`\n118\t\n119\t### Patch File Format\n120\t\n121\t```yaml\n122\t# .codeharness/workflows/default.patch.yaml\n123\textends: embedded://default\n124\t\n125\toverrides:\n126\t  tasks:\n127\t    implement:\n128\t      session: continue\n129\t      max_budget_usd: 5.0\n130\t\n131\treplace:\n132\t  flow:\n133\t    - implement\n134\t    - verify\n135\t```\n136\t\n137\t- `extends` — identifies the base (currently only `embedded://default` supported)\n138\t- `overrides` — deep-merged: objects merge recursively, arrays replace, scalars replace\n139\t- `replace` — full section replacement: keys in `replace` wholly overwrite corresponding keys in base\n140\t\n141\t### Merge Strategy\n142\t\n143\tThe `deepMerge` function already exists in `agent-resolver.ts` (lines 106-131). Same semantics:\n144\t- Objects: recursive merge\n145\t- Arrays: replace entirely\n146\t- Scalars: replace\n147\t\n148\tThe `replace` key is new (not in agent-resolver). After deep-merging `overrides`, each key in `replace` fully overwrites the corresponding key in the result. This allows replacing `flow` entirely without deep-merging individual steps.\n149\t\n150\t### Current run.ts Workflow Loading (lines 101-115)\n151\t\n152\t```typescript\n153\tconst projectWorkflowPath = join(projectDir, '.codeharness', 'workflows', 'default.yaml');\n154\tconst templateWorkflowPath = join(projectDir, 'templates', 'workflows', 'default.yaml');\n155\tconst workflowPath = existsSync(projectWorkflowPath) ? projectWorkflowPath : templateWorkflowPath;\n156\tparsedWorkflow = parseWorkflow(workflowPath);\n157\t```\n158\t\n159\tThis will be replaced with `resolveWorkflow({ cwd: projectDir })` which handles the full resolution chain internally. Note: if a project has a full custom workflow (not a patch) at `.codeharness/workflows/default.yaml`, the resolver should detect the absence of `extends` and load it directly (same pattern as custom agents in `agent-resolver.ts`).\n160\t\n161\t### Schema Validation\n162\t\n163\tThe workflow JSON schema (`src/schemas/workflow.schema.json`) has `\"additionalProperties\": false`. Patch files do NOT need to pass schema validation independently — only the merged result does. The `extends`, `overrides`, and `replace` keys are patch-specific and would fail schema validation if validated as a standalone workflow.\n164\t\n165\t### Existing Code to Reference\n166\t\n167\t- `src/lib/agent-resolver.ts` — `loadPatch()`, `mergePatch()`, `resolveAgent()`, `deepMerge()` — direct pattern to follow\n168\t- `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` — `parseWorkflow()` — existing function to keep backward-compatible\n169\t- `src/lib/schema-validate.ts` — `validateWorkflowSchema()` — reuse for post-merge validation\n170\t- `src/commands/run.ts` — lines 101-115 — call site to update\n171\t\n172\t### File Structure\n173\t\n174\t```\n175\tsrc/\n176\t  lib/\n177\t    workflow-parser.ts          (MODIFIED — add resolveWorkflow, loadWorkflowPatch, mergeWorkflowPatch)\n178\t    __tests__/\n179\t      workflow-parser.test.ts   (MODIFIED — add patch resolution tests)\n180\t  commands/\n181\t    run.ts                      (MODIFIED — use resolveWorkflow instead of parseWorkflow)\n182\t```\n183\t\n184\t### Dependencies\n185\t\n186\t- **Modified file:** `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` — add ~80-100 lines for patch resolution\n187\t- **Modified file:** `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-parser.test.ts` — add ~150-200 lines of new tests\n188\t- **Modified file:** `src/commands/run.ts` — ~5-10 line change\n189\t- **No new files** — patch resolution lives in the existing workflow-parser module\n190\t- **No new npm dependencies** — uses `yaml`, `node:fs`, `node:os` (already available)\n191\t\n192\t### Anti-Patterns to Avoid\n193\t\n194\t- **Do NOT create a separate `workflow-resolver.ts`** — per architecture, patch resolution is part of `workflow-parser` module (FR1-6, FR13-15 all map to same module)\n195\t- **Do NOT validate patch files against the workflow schema** — patches have `extends`/`overrides`/`replace` keys not in the schema; only validate the merged result\n196\t- **Do NOT break `parseWorkflow()`** — it must remain backward-compatible for direct file parsing\n197\t- **Do NOT use `any` in the API surface** — explicit TypeScript types per NFR18\n198\t- **Do NOT modify `workflow.schema.json`** — the schema defines valid workflows, not patch files\n199\t\n200\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n201\t\n202\tFrom story 3-3 (agent resolver):\n203\t- The `resolveAgent()` function follows embedded -> user -> project patch chain\n204\t- `loadPatch()` returns null for missing files (silent skip), throws for malformed YAML\n205\t- `mergePatch()` deep-merges `overrides` and appends `prompt_patches`\n206\t- Custom agents (no `extends`) are loaded directly — same pattern needed for custom workflows\n207\t\n208\tFrom story 2-2 (workflow parser):\n209\t- `parseWorkflow()` reads file, parses YAML, validates schema, checks referential integrity, applies defaults\n210\t- `WorkflowParseError` is the error class with `.errors` array\n211\t\n212\t### Git Intelligence\n213\t\n214\tRecent commits follow: `feat: story {key} — {description}`. This story modifies existing files (workflow-parser.ts, run.ts, tests). The codebase uses TypeScript with ESM `.js` extensions in import paths. Tests use vitest with temp directory patterns.\n215\t\n216\t### References\n217\t\n218\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 9.1: Workflow Patch Resolution]\n219\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD1: Module Boundaries — workflow-parser covers FR13-15]\n220\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD4: Config Resolution Caching]\n221\t- [Source: src/lib/agent-resolver.ts — loadPatch(), mergePatch(), resolveAgent(), deepMerge()]\n222\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-parser.ts — parseWorkflow(), WorkflowParseError]\n223\t- [Source: src/lib/schema-validate.ts — validateWorkflowSchema()]\n224\t- [Source: src/commands/run.ts — workflow loading (lines 101-115)]\n225\t- [Source: src/schemas/workflow.schema.json — workflow schema (additionalProperties: false)]\n226\t- [Source: templates/workflows/default.yaml — embedded default workflow]\n227\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PJjnh79Qyo3QtseYHMvmW1","session_id":"b82e0b02-3413-404d-8b3c-c5e48f86089c","uuid":"3519f56c-525b-4997-a444-73d715380319","timestamp":"2026-04-03T02:44:23.885Z"}
