{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PJjnh79Qyo3QtseYHMvmW1","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's the summary:\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Summary\n\n**Story 9.1: Workflow Patch Resolution** -- all 4 tasks complete, story marked `review`.\n\n### Files Modified\n\n1. **`/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/workflow-parser.ts`** -- Added ~140 lines:\n   - `WorkflowPatch` interface (`extends`, `overrides`, `replace`)\n   - `deepMerge()` -- same semantics as agent-resolver (objects merge recursively, arrays/scalars replace)\n   - `loadWorkflowPatch(filePath)` -- returns null on missing file, throws `WorkflowParseError` on malformed YAML\n   - `mergeWorkflowPatch(base, patch)` -- deep-merges `overrides`, then applies `replace` as full overwrites\n   - `resolveWorkflow(options?)` -- full embedded -> user -> project patch chain with schema validation and referential integrity checking\n\n2. **`/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/run.ts`** -- Replaced direct `parseWorkflow()` call with `resolveWorkflow({ cwd: projectDir })`, with fallback to `parseWorkflow()` for backward compatibility.\n\n3. **`/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/workflow-parser.test.ts`** -- Added ~200 lines of tests covering:\n   - `loadWorkflowPatch`: null on missing, throw on invalid YAML, throw on non-object, load valid patch\n   - `mergeWorkflowPatch`: overrides-only, replace-only, both, replace-wins-over-overrides\n   - `resolveWorkflow`: embedded-only, deep-merge overrides, replace semantics, user-before-project ordering, malformed YAML, schema validation after merge, dangling task refs, silent skip on missing, cwd option, full custom workflow\n\n4. **`/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts`** -- Added `resolveWorkflowMock` to the mock setup, updated test expectations to match new `resolveWorkflow` call path.\n\n5. **`/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/9-1-workflow-patch-resolution.md`** -- Status changed to `review`, all tasks/subtasks checked.\n\n### Test Results\n\n- Build: zero errors\n- Tests: 4193 passed, 0 failed, 161 test files (38 tests in workflow-parser alone, 20 new)\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- The user-level patch ordering test writes/restores `~/.codeharness/workflows/default.patch.yaml` on the real filesystem. If the test process crashes mid-execution, a stale patch file could remain at that path. A `vi.mock` of `os.homedir()` would be cleaner but would require refactoring `resolveWorkflow` to accept a home directory option. This is acceptable tech debt for now.\n- `deepMerge` is duplicated between `agent-resolver.ts` and `workflow-parser.ts`. The story noted this as acceptable (\"extract into shared location or duplicate inline\"), but it should be extracted to a shared utility in a future story to avoid drift.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 5, Read: 7, Edit: 13, Grep: 2, Glob: 1, Skill: 1, Write: 0, other: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npm run test:unit` run 2 (~800 lines of ANSI output), `npm run test:unit` run 1 (~600 lines), `npm run build` (~15 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none significant -- one file (workflow-parser.test.ts) was read twice (initial read + checking end of file for edit target)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ac87ea103d2fe9f53 (use SendMessage with to: 'ac87ea103d2fe9f53' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 86130\ntool_uses: 42\nduration_ms: 293624</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b82e0b02-3413-404d-8b3c-c5e48f86089c","uuid":"3f638404-74d1-4abc-9fd4-2fca7de233f6","timestamp":"2026-04-03T02:49:08.327Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-dev-story for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/9-1-workflow-patch-resolution.md — implement all tasks, wr